    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="218" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Matus</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Guzman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation—Handed to the
                                Secretary of State by the Nicaraguan minister, April 23,
                                1895.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 22,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>English war vessels are here to enforce the ultimatum. We have asked Lord
                            Kimberley by cable to await the instructions sent to our representative
                            in London for an amicable settlement of the difficulty. We are expecting
                            his reply. Request the Government of the United States to aid Nicaragua
                            in obtaining that.</p>
            </div>
